data.meta_description:
117 likes, 0 comments - changetheworld_mun on December 1, 2023: "On December 1, 1988, Benazir Bhutto was nominated to become the prime minister of Pakistan, the first woman and the youngest person to govern a Muslim nation.

Despite a turbulent career, with accusations of corruption, years after her assassination in Rawalpindi, her legacy and significance continue to hold a special place in the hearts of the millions of Muslim women and girls who aspire to change the world.".
